title: _Begriffsschrift_ Chapter III Member of sequence
content: ` p ( ( t+ `` R ) u. _I ) c ` means ` c ` is a member of the ` R ` -sequence begining with ` p ` and ` p ` is a member of the ` R ` -sequence ending with ` c ` . ~ dffrege99 through ~ frege114 develop this. This will be shown to be related to the transitive-reflexive closure of relation ` R ` . But more work needs to be done on transitive closure of relations before this is ready for Metamath.

blocks.name: dffrege99
blocks.content: If ` Z ` is identical with ` X ` or follows ` X ` in the ` R ` -sequence, then we say : " ` Z ` belongs to the ` R ` -sequence beginning with ` X ` " or " ` X ` belongs to the ` R ` -sequence ending with ` Z ` ". Definition 99 of [Frege1879] p. 71. (Contributed by RP, 2-Jul-2020.)

blocks.name: frege102
blocks.content: If ` Z ` belongs to the ` R ` -sequence beginning with ` X ` , then every result of an application of the procedure ` R ` to ` Z ` follows ` X ` in the ` R ` -sequence. Proposition 102 of [Frege1879] p. 72. (Contributed by RP, 7-Jul-2020.) (Proof modification is discouraged.)

thm frege104(class c0, class c1, class c2, class c3) {
  |- wi(wbr(c0, cun(cfv(ctcl, c1), cid), c2), wi(wn(wbr(c0, cfv(ctcl, c1), c2)), wceq(c0, c2)))
  -| wcel(c2, c3)
} = {
  ax-mp(wi(wbr(c0, cun(cfv(ctcl, c1), cid), c2), wi(wn(wbr(c0, cfv(ctcl, c1), c2)), wceq(c0, c2))), wi(wceq(c2, c0), wceq(c0, c2)))
  vtocl(hs0, c2, wi(wceq(c2, c0), wceq(c0, c2)), wi(wceq(cv(hs0), c0), wceq(c0, cv(hs0))))
  elexi(c2, c3)
  imbi12d(wceq(cv(hs0), c2), wceq(cv(hs0), c0), wceq(c0, cv(hs0)), wceq(c2, c0), wceq(c0, c2))
  eqeq1(cv(hs0), c2, c0)
  eqeq2(cv(hs0), c2, c0)
  frege55c(hs0, c0)
  frege103(c2, c0, c1, c3)
  diff.hs0.c(c2)
  diff.hs0.w(wi(wceq(c2, c0), wceq(c0, c2)))
}
blocks.pretty:
thm frege104(class c0, class c1, class c2, class c3) {
  ⊢ (c0[((t+ ` c1)⋃ =)]c2 →(¬ c0[(t+ ` c1)]c2 → c0 = c2))
  ⊣ c2 ∈ c3
} = {
  ax-mp((c0[((t+ ` c1)⋃ =)]c2 →(¬ c0[(t+ ` c1)]c2 → c0 = c2)), (c2 = c0 → c0 = c2))
  vtocl(hs0, c2, (c2 = c0 → c0 = c2), (hs0 = c0 → c0 = hs0))
  elexi(c2, c3)
  imbi12d(hs0 = c2, hs0 = c0, c0 = hs0, c2 = c0, c0 = c2)
  eqeq1(hs0, c2, c0)
  eqeq2(hs0, c2, c0)
  frege55c(hs0, c0)
  frege103(c2, c0, c1, c3)
  diff.hs0.c(c2)
  diff.hs0.w((c2 = c0 → c0 = c2))
}

blocks.name: frege106

blocks.name: frege108
blocks.content: If ` Y ` belongs to the ` R ` -sequence beginning with ` Z ` , then every result of an application of the procedure ` R ` to ` Y ` belongs to the ` R ` -sequence beginning with ` Z ` . Proposition 108 of [Frege1879] p. 74. (Contributed by RP, 7-Jul-2020.) (Proof modification is discouraged.)

blocks.name: frege109
blocks.content: The property of belonging to the ` R ` -sequence beginning with ` X ` is hereditary in the ` R ` -sequence. Proposition 109 of [Frege1879] p. 74. (Contributed by RP, 7-Jul-2020.) (Proof modification is discouraged.)

  df-br(c1, cun(cfv(ctcl, c0), cid), cv(hs0))
  elimasn(cv(hs0), cun(cfv(ctcl, c0), cid), c1)

  imbi2i(wbr(cv(hs0), c0, cv(hs1)), wbr(c1, cun(cfv(ctcl, c0), cid), cv(hs1)), wcel(cv(hs1), cima(cun(cfv(ctcl, c0), cid), csn(c1))))
  bitr4i(wbr(c1, cun(cfv(ctcl, c0), cid), cv(hs1)), wcel(cv(hs1), cima(cun(cfv(ctcl, c0), cid), csn(c1))), wcel(cop(c1, cv(hs1)), cun(cfv(ctcl, c0), cid)))
  df-br(c1, cun(cfv(ctcl, c0), cid), cv(hs1))
  elimasn(cv(hs1), cun(cfv(ctcl, c0), cid), c1)
  elexi(c1, c2)
  vex(hs1)
  diff.hs0.s(hs1)
  diff.hs0.c(cima(cun(cfv(ctcl, c0), cid), csn(c1)))
  diff.hs0.c(c0)
  diff.hs1.c(cima(cun(cfv(ctcl, c0), cid), csn(c1)))
  diff.hs1.c(c0)
  diff.hs1.w(wcel(cv(hs0), cima(cun(cfv(ctcl, c0), cid), csn(c1))))
}

  bitr4i(wcel(c3, cima(cun(cfv(ctcl, c1), cid), csn(c2))), wbr(c2, cun(cfv(ctcl, c1), cid), c3), wcel(cop(c2, c3), cun(cfv(ctcl, c1), cid)))

blocks.name: frege111
blocks.content: If ` Y ` belongs to the ` R ` -sequence beginning with ` Z ` , then every result of an application of the procedure ` R ` to ` Y ` belongs to the ` R ` -sequence beginning with ` Z ` or precedes ` Z ` in the ` R ` -sequence. Proposition 111 of [Frege1879] p. 75. (Contributed by RP, 7-Jul-2020.) (Revised by RP, 8-Jul-2020.) (Proof modification is discouraged.)

blocks.name: frege112

blocks.name: frege114
